    "narrative": "The offensive outlook for Ghost Ride the WHIP centers on a high-upside trio of **Tyler Soderstrom** (76.91), **Vinnie Pasquantino** (76.21), and **Mickey Moniak** (75.75). **Tyler Soderstrom** draws the premier matchup of the day, capitalizing on a 10% park factor boost and a favorable encounter with Leiter to anchor our production. Meanwhile, **Vinnie Pasquantino** and **Mickey Moniak** both benefit from elite SP skill ratings against suspect arms in Montero and Weiss respectively; **Mickey Moniak** in particular sees his value elevated by a dynamic platoon advantage that makes him a must-start despite his mid-order placement. We are also tracking **Brice Turang** closely; while his score of 64.27 is bolstered by his batting order, his active status as a primary source of speed against a slow-working Corbin makes him our most critical weapon in the scarcity-heavy stolen base category.\n\nRisk management remains a priority given the volatility of today\u2019s matchups. **James Wood** (55.43) sits near our marginal threshold due to the aggressive base-stealing prevention tactics used by Ashcraft, which effectively suppress his utility despite his leadoff spot. **Jose Caballero** remains a productive play (63.52) thanks to his specific platoon edge against Suter, but we are keeping a close eye on the bench, where we are currently light on depth due to scheduled off-days for **Corbin Carroll**, **Austin Riley**, **Seiya Suzuki**, and **Trevor Story**. Given these vacancies, we lack the immediate pinch-hit depth to pivot if **Luis Campusano** (43.78) fails to produce from the bottom of the order, though his presence is necessary to maintain game caps. Should our reserves like **Gabriel Moreno**, **Max Muncy**, or **Dalton Rushing** see late-inning usage, we will need to re-evaluate their availability for the weekend. We are also monitoring prospect depth assets like **Zach McKinstry**, **Alex Freeland**, **Carson Williams**, and **Travis Bazzana** for potential roster adjustments should current starters hit a wall against the tougher arms like Castillo.",
